<div id="banner">
	<h1>Shrub Wants to Stop Wildfires by Stopping Forests </h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Sorry for all the political announcements, but this one was too crazy to pass up.  Heritage Forests Campaign <a href="http://actionnetwork.org/campaign/healthy_forests">has  a letter-sending service</a> to tell your senators to stop the Shrub&#8217;s &#8220;Healthy Forests Initiative&#8221; which basically eliminates all the environmental protections for forests we&#8217;ve had, in the name of trying to protect them from wildfires. It&#8217;s absurd and you should let your representatives know that.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 28, 2002 08:29 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_politics">Politics</a>)  <a href="000539" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

